Detailed Description

cvmx_ndf_cmd

When software reads this register, NDF_MISC[RD_VAL] is cleared to 0. Software must always write all eight bytes whenever it writes this register. If there are fewer than eight bytes left in the command sequence that software wants the NAND flash controller to execute, it must insert Idle (WAIT) commands to make up eight bytes. Software must also ensure that there is enough space in the NDF_CMD queue to accept these eight bytes by first reading NDF_MISC[FR_BYT].

Sixty-four-bit operations must be used to access this register.
